    <h1>Persian Cat Care Guide</h1>
    <p><strong>Breed:</strong> Persian Cat</p>
    <p><strong>Age:</strong> 12-17 years (average lifespan)</p>
    <p><strong>Size:</strong> Medium to large</p>
    
    <h3>General Care Tips:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Exercise: Persian cats are relatively low-energy. Provide plenty of indoor playtime and cozy spaces.</li>
        <li>Diet: A high-protein diet with some fats for their coats is ideal.</li>
        <li>Grooming: They require daily grooming to prevent matting in their long fur.</li>
        <li>Health: Regular vet visits are important to monitor for common health issues such as kidney problems.</li>
    </ul>
    
